16:41.400 --> 16:43.766
I think I like your Olive Theory.

16:44.436 --> 16:46.927
I think I like your new French horn.

16:47.439 --> 16:49.407
I think I like your nose.

16:50.843 --> 16:52.470
I think I'm in love with you.

16:52.578 --> 16:53.567
What?

16:53.679 --> 16:54.646
What?

16:54.747 --> 16:55.714
What?

16:55.948 --> 16:58.007
Come on, man, you said your stomach's
been hurting, right?

16:58.117 --> 17:01.883
You know what that is? Hunger.
You're hungry for experience.

17:01.987 --> 17:05.888
Hungry for something new.
Hungry for olives.

17:06.325 --> 17:08.816
But you're too scared
to do anything about it.

17:08.926 --> 17:10.952
Yeah, I'm scared, okay?

17:12.464 --> 17:15.865
But when I think of spending
the rest of my life with Lily,

17:15.968 --> 17:18.492
committing forever, no other women,

17:19.605 --> 17:21.539
doesn't scare me at all.

17:22.207 --> 17:24.071
I'm marrying that girl.

17:25.676 --> 17:26.769
Lily.

17:27.613 --> 17:29.376
Lily, I like olives.

17:30.382 --> 17:32.077
We'll make it work.

17:34.319 --> 17:35.718
(SIGHING)

17:44.129 --> 17:46.927
So, Orlando? You gonna hit Disney World?

17:48.367 --> 17:50.460
- You love me?
- Oh, God.

17:51.170 --> 17:53.638
I can't believe I said that.
Why did I say that?

17:53.739 --> 17:55.229
Who says that?

17:55.774 --> 17:57.867
- I should just go.
- Hold on.

17:58.477 --> 17:59.944
Wait a minute.

18:02.347 --> 18:03.678
I promised you these.

18:03.816 --> 18:04.805
- Olives.
- Yeah.

18:04.917 --> 18:06.714
Thanks. I love you.

18:06.819 --> 18:08.650
What is wrong with me?

18:10.589 --> 18:13.387
Why are we still sitting here? Let's go.
We can still make last call.

18:13.492 --> 18:16.928
What do you say, Lil?
"Yo-ho-ho, and a bottle of rum"?

18:19.665 --> 18:23.294
- 'Cause you're a pirate?
- Okay, eye patch gone.

18:23.802 --> 18:25.793
And we can't just abandon Ted.

18:26.004 --> 18:28.996
If it doesn't go well up there,
he's gonna need some support.

18:29.108 --> 18:32.043
It's been, like, 20 minutes.
Do you think they're doing it?

18:32.144 --> 18:33.668
You think they're doing it
in front of the dogs?

18:33.779 --> 18:35.371
Doggie style.

18:35.647 --> 18:37.740
I knew this girl in college,
she had this Golden Retriever...

18:37.850 --> 18:39.943
Okay, we can go to the bar.
Just stop talking.

18:40.052 --> 18:41.314
Hit it, Ranjit.

18:46.758 --> 18:48.851
So, when you tell this story
to your friends,

18:48.961 --> 18:50.895
could you avoid the word "psycho"?

18:51.196 --> 18:53.391
I'd prefer "eccentric."

18:54.299 --> 18:56.164
Goodnight, psycho.

19:00.906 --> 19:01.873
Great.

19:02.274 --> 19:04.401
- How do I get to the F train?
- Oh.

19:05.410 --> 19:08.743
- Two blocks, that way and take a right.
- Thanks.

19:11.650 --> 19:13.140
You know what?

19:14.286 --> 19:17.551
I'm done being single. I'm not good at it.

19:17.956 --> 19:20.584
Look, obviously,
you can't tell a woman you just met

19:20.692 --> 19:24.458
you love her, but it sucks that you can't.

19:25.931 --> 19:27.831
I'll tell you something, though. If a woman,

19:27.933 --> 19:30.766
not you, just some hypothetical woman,

19:30.869 --> 19:33.531
were to bear with me through all this,

19:33.639 --> 19:37.075
I think I'd make a damn good husband
because that's the stuff I'd be good at.

19:37.176 --> 19:41.044
Stuff like making her laugh
and being a good father

19:42.047 --> 19:44.607
and walking her five hypothetical dogs.

19:46.118 --> 19:47.642
Being a good kisser.

19:48.854 --> 19:52.813
- Everyone thinks they're a good kisser.
- Oh, I've got references.

19:53.559 --> 19:55.049
Goodnight, Ted.

20:01.200 --> 20:05.364
- And I'm a good handshaker.
- That's a pretty great handshake.

20:09.608 --> 20:12.839
And that was it.
I'll probably never see her again.

20:15.781 --> 20:17.681
- What?
- That was the signal.

20:17.783 --> 20:21.310
That long, lingering handshake.
You should've kissed her.

20:21.787 --> 20:24.278
There's no such thing as the signal.

20:24.389 --> 20:26.653
But, yeah, that was the signal.

20:26.792 --> 20:27.952
Signal.

20:29.661 --> 20:32.596
Carl, thank you.
There's something I gotta do.

20:33.799 --> 20:36.359
By the way, you should've kissed her.

20:36.668 --> 20:38.829
Carl, you guys weren't there.

20:40.572 --> 20:42.665
I am so turned on right now.

20:43.642 --> 20:46.440
Guys, trust me. I've seen the signal.

20:46.745 --> 20:50.613
- That was not the signal.
- Yeah, Ted, we're not on you anymore.

20:51.283 --> 20:54.616
- To my fiancée.
- To the future.

20:54.720 --> 20:56.585
To one hell of a night.

21:00.092 --> 21:02.026
That was not the signal.

21:03.428 --> 21:07.364
<i>I asked her about it years later,</i>
<i>and, yeah, that was the signal,</i>

21:07.466 --> 21:08.865
<i>I could've kissed her,</i>

21:08.967 --> 21:12.801
<i>But that's the funny thing about destiny,</i>
<i>it happens whether you plan it or not,</i>

21:12.904 --> 21:14.929
<i>I mean, I never thought</i>
<i>I'd see that girl again,</i>

21:15.040 --> 21:16.166
<i>But it turns out,</i>

21:16.275 --> 21:19.403
<i>I was just too close to the puzzle</i>
<i>to see the picture that was forming,</i>

21:19.511 --> 21:21.979
Because that, kids, is the true story

21:22.080 --> 21:24.241
of how I met your Aunt Robin.

21:25.317 --> 21:26.841
Aunt Robin?

21:26.952 --> 21:28.715
I thought this was how you met Mom.

21:28.820 --> 21:30.845
Will you relax? I'm getting to it.

21:31.390 --> 21:34.689
Like I said, it's a long story.

